I visit Chop Society every week or 2, although I haven't been inside since they changed from being Niko's last year. Instead I use their drive thru, which I would bet most people don't even know is there. (You drive around the back of the building to the far, hidden side. It is neither well-marked nor well-lit. Even their menu sign with speaker  is dimly lit and easy to miss.) The wait time at the window is the same as if you were waiting inside for your food to be cooked....So don't go expecting a McDonald's wait.  It is my go-to place for a good tasty salad...a Greek one. (Don't worry...no anchovies.) It's not fancy, just really fresh. It's always served with a large pita. And you can order it plain or with your choice of meat...I like the gyro shavings they pile on. It's also nice to order a cup of soup on the side from time to time. Again, not fancy. It's just nice to get a warm bit of soup at a drive thru on a cold night. I think they make it fresh. Altho the chicken noodle is not noodles, it's over-cooked macaroni shells. Their large-portioned Denver omelet is also good and served with buttered toast of your choice. So if you're looking for a take-out you don't have to get out of your car or pajamas to pick up, try Chop Society. The employee at the window is always pleasant no matter how you're dressed.
